HEADWORD: Umbellularia
<hw>Um*bel`lu*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Umbellule</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus
of deep-sea alcyonaria consisting of a cluster of large flowerlike
polyps situated at the summit of a long, slender stem which stands
upright in the mud, supported by a bulbous base.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umbellule</ent>⟦br⟧
